The paper deals with the algorithmic randomness of sequences and their constructive dimensions, which are concepts related to computational complexity and information theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the study of sequences and their properties, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of Turing reductions, which is a topic in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
